ROS install algorithm on Ubuntu

1- Download virtualbox or VMware
2- Download ubuntu on virtule box or VMware
3- Open Ubuntu, then open the Terminal from Ubuntu
4- Open ROS.org, then choose version 20.04, then choose Ubuntu
5- After opening the ubuntu page on the ros.org website, copy the following commands and paste them into the terminal one by one
First: sudo sh -c 'echo "deb http://packages.ros.org/ros/ubuntu $(lsb_release -sc) main"> /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ros-latest.list "
Second: sudo apt install curl
Third: curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ros/rosdistro/master/ros.asc | sudo apt-key add -
Fourth: sudo apt update
Fifth: sudo apt install ros-noetic-desktop-full
Sixth: sudo apt install ros-noetic-desktop
Seventh: sudo apt install ros-noetic-ros-base
Eighth: sudo apt install ros-noetic-PACKAGE
Ninth: sudo apt install ros-noetic-slam-gmapping
Tenth: apt search ros-noetic
Eleventh: source /opt/ros/noetic/setup.bash
Twelfth: echo "source /opt/ros/noetic/setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
Thirteenth: echo "source /opt/ros/noetic/setup.zsh" >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc
Fourteenth: sudo apt install python3-rosdep python3-rosinstall python3-rosinstall-generator python3-wstool build-essential
Fifteenth: sudo apt install python3-rosdep
And finally to configure ros on Ubuntu
Sixteenth: sudo rosdep init
rosdep update
